<section class="tool-header">
  <%= render partial: 'pages/shared/navbar' %>
  <% @active_tab = 'Quill Connect' %>
  <% @tool = 'connect' %>
  <%= render partial: "pages/shared/tools_anchor_navbar", active_tab: @active_tab, tool: @tool%>
</section>
<div class="tool-container connect-tool-page">

    <section class='bg-connect-yellow tool-hero text-center tool-section'>
      <h1 class="q-h1">
          <img class="tool-page-icon lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/shared/quill_connect_white.svg"%>>Quill Connect
      </h1>
      <p class='description'>
      Help your students advance from writing fragments and run-ons to composing complex, well-structured sentences with Quill Connect. By combining sentences, students learn how to demonstrate relationships between ideas. Then, they receive instant, custom feedback designed to help them improve the clarity and precision of their sentences.
      </p>
      <section class="tool-ctas connect-tool">
        <a href=<%= "#{ENV['QUILL_CONNECT_URL']}/#/play/lesson/-KnoWhUWhtxvet4_bi4r" %> target="_blank" class="q-button cta-button bg-white text-connect-yellow">Try a sample activity</a>
        <% if current_user&.teacher? %>
          <a href='/assign/activity-library?activityClassificationFilters[]=connect' class="q-button text-white learn-more-button">Assign</a>
        <% end %>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section class="tool-animation-section " id="overview">
          <video class='tool-animation lazy' data-src=<%="#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/videos/tools/connect.mp4"%> autoplay loop/>
    </section>

    <section class="walk-thru-wrapper desktop" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="walk-thru-step flex-row vertically-centered">
          <div class="content-wrapper flex-row space-between vertically-centered">
              <div class="prompt">
                <p class="prompt-header">
                  PROMPT
                </p>
                <p class="prompt-text">Patrick Henry opposed new British taxes.</p>
                <p class="prompt-text">He gave a speech.</p>
                <p class="prompt-text">The speech was powerful.</p>
                <p class="prompt-text">The speech was to inspire the colonists.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="blurb introduction">
                  <h2>How Quill Connect Gives Feedback</h2>
                  <p>
                  Students are prompted with four ideas and asked to join them together. There are many different ways of combining them, and Quill serves feedback on hundreds of potential answers. Here is a student&apos;s progression from their first attempt to a strong sentence.
                  </p>
              </div>
          </div>
      </div>
        <div class="walk-thru-step flex-row vertically-centered">
            <div class="content-wrapper flex-row space-between vertically-centered">
                <img class="arrow arrow-1 lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/arrow_1.png" %>>
                <img class="negative-left-margin lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/attempt_1.png" %> alt="connect image">
                <div class="blurb blurb-attempt-1">
                    <h2><span>1st Attempt:</span> Write Concisely</h2>
                    <p>
                    The student used <span>and</span> to join multiple ideas together. This is a very common pattern for emerging writers. Quill breaks this pattern by challenging students to revise their work.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="walk-thru-step flex-row vertically-centered">
            <div class="content-wrapper flex-row space-between vertically-centered">
              <img class="negative-left-margin lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/attempt_2.png"%> alt="connect image">
                <div class="blurb blurb-attempt-2">
                    <h2><span>2nd Attempt:</span> Show Relationships</h2>
                    <p>
                    While using <span>and</span> to join the two main ideas is grammatically correct, it is not the strongest way of conveying the relationship between these ideas. Students are prompted to use a conjunction that expresses a cause and effect relationship. This is an important step towards conveying complex ideas.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <img class="arrow arrow-2 lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/arrow_2.png" %>>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="walk-thru-step flex-row vertically-centered">
            <div class="content-wrapper flex-row space-between vertically-centered">
              <img class="arrow arrow-3 lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/arrow_3.png" %>>
              <img class="negative-left-margin img-attempt-3 lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/attempt_3.png" %> alt="connect image">
                <div class="blurb blurb-attempt-3">
                    <h2><span>3rd Attempt:</span> Use Punctuation</h2>
                    <p>
                      The student showed the correct relationship but left out the comma. Quill provides feedback and shows a model sentence to help guide the student.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="walk-thru-step flex-row vertically-centered">
            <div class="content-wrapper flex-row space-between vertically-centered">
              <img class="negative-left-margin img-attempt-4 lazyload" loading="lazy" src=<%= "#{ENV['CDN_URL']}/images/tools/connect/attempt_4.png" %> alt="connect image">
                <div class="blurb blurb-attempt-4">
                    <h2><span>4th Attempt:</span> Strong Sentence!</h2>
                    <p>
                      The student wrote a clear and concise sentence!
                    </p>
                    <p>
                      Quill provides additional feedback to reinforce what the student learned.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
